## Shared infrastructure (not capability slices)

These live flat in `application/` and are NOT capability slices:

- `core/` — pure models, protocols, rules (no framework deps, no SKILL.md)
- `stores/` — persistence port implementations (mem, pg, world model)
- `tools/` — agent tool providers (query, documents, mutations)
- `events/` — event feed HTTP polling + WebSocket push

## Relationship to `.cursor/skills/`

`.cursor/skills/` is for **dev infrastructure skills** — how to build and extend
the platform (add-agent, add-query-operation, ingestion-debugging, platform-orientation).
These are for Cursor AI, not for REMI agents. No corresponding `application/<name>/` entry.

`application/<capability>/references/IMPL.md` serves both audiences — the REMI agent
asking "how do I access this?" and the developer asking "which files do I touch?".

## What not to do

- Do not put skills in `.remi/skills/` — they belong in `application/<capability>/`
- Do not put `IMPL.md` or `DATA.md` as siblings of `SKILL.md` — they belong in `references/`
- Do not create skill directories without referencing the supporting files in `SKILL.md`
- Do not organize capabilities into subdirectories — flat: `application/<name>/SKILL.md`
- Do not leave agent manifests in `src/remi/application/agents/` — migrate to `scripts/app.yaml`
